text: Keitele is a municipality in Northern Savonia, Finland. In January 2014, 2,430 people lived there. The municipalities next to it are Pielavesi, Pihtipudas, Tervo, Vesanto and Viitasaari. The municipality was established in 1879, but camp sites been found from the 1300s. == Villages == Hamula, Koutajärvi, Kukertaja, Leppäselkä, Pahkamäki, Petäjäkylä, Sulkavanjärvi, Tossavanlahti, Viinikkala, Vuonamo, Äyräpää and Hemminki. == Other websites == * Category:Municipalities of North Savo Category:1879 establishments in Europe Category:1870s establishments in Finland
